
1 - Install Eclipse for C/C++ Embedded.

2 – Install python 3.

3 – Install pyocd with ***pip3 install pyocd***

4 – Download [xPack gcc](https://xpack.github.io/dev-tools/arm-none-eabi-gcc/releases/), extract it somewhere, ex. ***c:\xpack\xpack-arm-none-eabi-gcc-14.2.1-1.1***.

5 – Download [xPack build tools](https://github.com/xpack-dev-tools/windows-build-tools-xpack/releases/), extract t it somewhere, ex. ***c:\xpack\xpack-windows-build-tools-4.4.1-3***.

6 – Eclipse -> Window -> Preferences -> MCU -> \
`     `Global Arm Toolchains Paths: \
`         `Toolchain folder: ***C:\xpack\xpack-arm-none-eabi-gcc-14.2.1-1.1\bin***.\
`         `Default toolchain: xPack GNU Arm Embedded GCC

![](data:image/png;base64,)

`     `Global Build Tools Path: Build tools folder:  ***C:\xpack\xpack-windows-build-tools-4.4.1-3\bin***.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

\
7 – Eclipse -> Help -> Marketplace, install EmbSysRegView plugin, close the IDE.\
`      `(search on full name  ‘embsysregview’  and install)

![](data:image/png;base64,)\
\
8 – Place ***Puya.PY32F0xx\_DFP.2.9.0.pack***  in ***C:\Users\<user>\AppData\Roaming\CMSIS-Packs***.\
\
9 – Temporary rename the file from **.pack** to **.zip**, extract the SVD files somewhere, then rename it to .pack again.\
\
10 – Go to ***C:\Users\<user>\.p2\pool\plugins\org.eclipse.cdt.embsysregview.data\_0.2.6.r191\data\SVD(CMSIS)***\
`       `Create the folder "Puya". Place the **SVD** files file inside it, change the extension to **xml**.\
\
9 – Open Eclipse -> Window -> Preferences -> C/C++ -> Debug -> Embsys Register View\
`      `Architecture: SVD;   Vendor: Puya;   Chip: PY32F030xx 

![](data:image/png;base64,)\
\
10 – Eclipse -> New -> C/C++ Project -> C Managed build -> Empty project, Arm Cross GCC \
`        `-> Should use the toolchain be set earlier -> Finish

![](data:image/png;base64,)      ![](data:image/png;base64,)\
\
11 – Right click on project -> C/C++ Build \
`        `Builder Setings -> Builder type:  External Builder

![](data:image/png;base64,)\


Behaviour -> Enable parallel build

![](data:image/png;base64,)\


`     `Settings->Target Processor-> ***cortexm0-plus***.

![](data:image/png;base64,)\
`     `Settings -> Optimization -> Other optimization flags:\
`      `***-Wl,--cref -Wl,--gc-sections -static --specs=nano.specs -mfloat-abi=soft -mthumb \
`      `-Wl,--start-group -lc -lm -Wl,--end-group***\
`     `(Apply this to both Debug and Release profiles). This saves a lot of space, it's what CubeIDE uses.

12 – Eclipse -> Window -> Preferences -> MCU -> Global pyOCD Path\
`     `Executable: ***pyocd.exe***\
`     `Folder:  ***C:\Python\Scripts***   *( for global install Python )*\
***// C:\Users\<user>\AppData\Local\Packages\PythonSoftwareFoundation.Python.3.xxx\LocalCache\local-packages\Python3xx\Scripts  ( for local install Python )***

![](data:image/png;base64,)

\
\
13 - Click on the Debug button->Debug configurations->Create New GDB PyOCD -> Debugger tab\
`       `Click override target: ***py32f030x6***\
`       `Other options: ***--pack=C:\Users\<user>\AppData\Roaming\CMSIS-Packs\Puya.PY32F0xx\_DFP.2.9.0.pack***

![](data:image/png;base64,)

\
Linker script is set in Project properties->C/C++ Build->Settings->GNU Arm Cross Linker->General\
It's common to have a startup file in asm, Eclipse only takes assembler files with .S extension, must be uppercase!\
\
Debugging and programmign works, but EmbSys won't show the register data by default, you must first enable each by double-clicking on the reg name, it'll become green, now you can write and read to it.
